content.description: Sit-start to Jugfest. Bear hug the tufa and slap upward.
content.protection: Tight belay or boulder pad will keep you from falling 6-8 inches onto your delicate bum.

content.description: New route with 3 glueins and mussy hook anchors.The crux is between #2 and #3
content.protection: 3 ClimbTech Wave bolts to Mussy Hook anchors
content.location: About 25 feet to the right of Hidden Pockets and up a 3 foot ledge

content.description: Really sharp rock thru 3 bolts to a stand up clipping of the anchorsThis route has harder toproute variations to its left
content.protection: 3 ClimbTech Wave bolts to Mussy Hook Anchors
content.location: About 10 feet to the right of Squidward

content.description: This is one of the best 5.8's at Reimers!  It starts on a huge, blobby tufa and follows three bolts up to the roof.
content.location: On the right side of Landfill Wall.  One of the first routes you will find as you walk up to the wall.

climbs.name: Hidden Pockets
climbs.fa: Tommy Blackwell, Luke Bowman, Evan Jackson

content.description:
Just right (around the corner) of Jugfest. Guidebook gives it an R rating. I respectfully disagree.  

  I think clipping bolt #1 on Jugfest is sketchier than the "run out" to bolt 3 on this route.

Short routes but shadier than other popular walls.Watch for poison ivy!From left to right:Jugfest 5.8 (5.11 variation, Tufafest, start under that sweet hanging tufa)Hidden Pockets 5.8RSquidward 5.11Spongebob 5.7
